         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To emperor Caesar Marcus Aurelius Severus <supplied reason="lost">Alexander</supplied> <note>erased</note> Pius Felix Augustus <supplied reason="lost">and 
               Julia Mamaea Augusta, mother of Augustus</supplied> <note>erased</note> and of the camps. Marcus A<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 
               <supplied reason="lost">centurion of Legion III Augusta Pia Vindex <note>erased</note> Sev</supplied>eriana, placed in command of the detachment of the same legion, 
               built the fort from its foundations, using the same detachment.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Lines 1, 3-4: Erased after Alexander's <foreign xml:lang="la">damnatio</foreign> in 235.</p>
            <p>Line 6: It is not certain whether the erasure of the name of the legion is deliberate and is to be attributed to its damnatio in 238.</p>
         </div>
